b'CONCENTRATION AREAS'
b'Environmental and Water Resources Engineering'
b'Environmental Engineering and Water Resources\xc2\xa0covers the science and design of water treatment systems that support the society, as well as design of hydraulic structures and systems to handle hydrologic flow.'
b'Core Elective Courses:'
b'\nCME 403\n'
b'CME 403'
b'\nCME 421\n'
b'CME 421'
b'\nCME 422\n'
b'CME 422'
b'\nCME 427\n'
b'CME 427'
b'Geotechnical Engineering'
b'Geotechnical Engineering\xc2\xa0includes the fundamentals of foundation analysis and design, site characterization, analysis and design of shallow and deep foundations and earth retaining structures, environmental laws and regulations, sources of environmental contamination and waste treatment options.'
b'Core Elective Courses:'
b'\nCME 405\n'
b'CME 405'
b'\nCME 415\n'
b'CME 415'
b'\nCME 425\n'
b'CME 425'
b'Structural Engineering'
b'Structural Engineering includes design of metal, masonry, wood and reinforced concrete buildings and\xc2\xa0structures, bridge design, pre-stressed concrete design, advanced methods of structural analysis and preparation for passing the PE and SE exams.'
b'Core Elective Courses:'
b'\nCME 400\n'
b'CME 400'
b'\nCME 401\n'
b'CME 401'
b'\nCME 406\n'
b'CME 406'
b'\nCME 409\n'
b'CME 409'
b'\nCME 410\n'
b'CME 410'
b'Transportation Engineering'
b'Transportation Engineering covers geometric design of highways, traffic engineering and control, study of driver, vehicle and roadway system characteristics, intersection design and operation, highway capacity analysis and traffic signal design.'
b'Core Elective Courses:'
b'\nCME 402\n'
b'CME 402'
